of these courtyards contains various structures and/or shrines of differing levels of importance. the tiered, black-thatched roofs that you see on temples are made from a palm fibre, and this material is not permitted to be used for any roof other than those on temples. the elegant, pagoda-like tiered structure is itself called a meru (named after sacred mount meru (mahameru), the home of the gods), and the most dramatic of them can consist of as many as 11 tiers. the number of tiers, though, is always an odd number. example of a typical balinese temple layout the temple entrance 